{"type": "article", "id": 29373, "title": "展现花茎的金属花瓶", "description": "", "date": "2016-07-10T23:02:57Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [], "category": 25, "column": 28, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 1, "praise_count": 16, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160710210746eWXCLStTKDH5YPmq.jpg", "contents": "<p>          </p><p>除了花朵之外，花茎也可以作为一种装饰元素出现，以色列设计师 <a href=\"http://omerpolak.com/\">Omer Polak</a> 以日式的传统花道为灵感，制作了这款镂空的花瓶 165/114/21。所有花瓶均为手工制作，镂空的黄铜板被卷曲成筒状插入用来固定的大理石中，花束则穿过圆洞固定在底座的水槽之中，能够从侧面可以看到它的每个部分，带给人一种纤细的美感。Polak 希望通过这个设计让人们无需成为花道专家也能够利用这个花瓶发挥自己的想象力，感受到与自然的联系。你可以通过<a href=\"http://omerpolak.com/Ikebana-Vases-no-165-114-21\">链接</a>中的联络邮箱订购这款花瓶。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-active medium-insert-images-wide\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160710210843kKnSmrCHANcgtv4a.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.665672\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"medium-insert-image-active\">\n<figcaption class=\"medium-insert-caption-placeholder\"></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2016071021084378ultk4HAXriRwNz.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.498507\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160710210844ijZVPrI2vdH4aCUg.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.641791\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160710210844ifUO8BK0ZAwTrbNy.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.665672\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div>"}